The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Infosys in 3-year pact with Microsoft 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Infosys in 3-year pact with Microsoft 
                            
	Bangalore, April 14 (PTI): Infosys Technologies today said it had signed an agreement with Microsoft to manage internal IT services of the software giant globally.        
	As part of this three-year agreement, Infosys will streamline implementation processes, simplify support and service, and lower enterprise costs by using latest Microsoft solutions such as Windows 7, the Bangalore-based company said.        
	The infotech firm will deliver this engagement on an outcome-based pricing model, enabling Microsoft to associate and manage infotech costs directly to business variables and demand, Sanjay Jalona, Infosys vice-president and head of manufacturing for North America, said.        
	Infosys will provide Microsoft with infotech help desk, desk-side services and infrastructure and application support from multiple global centres.         
	It will manage Microsofts internal IT services for applications, devices and databases in 450 locations across 104 countries.        
	Infosys will establish a dedicated service excellence office to help Microsoft implement ISO 20000 and ITSM Processes, the statement said.        
	This agreement provides Infosys with an unique opportunity to partner Microsoft and gain deep and early expertise in the implementation and management of the latest Microsoft technologies, and thus enhancing Infosys capabilities to help other customers leverage Microsofts innovation and adopt these technologies, it said.        
	Infosys has partnered Unisys to provide global desk-side support and service desk.                                                                                                                                      
